docs.lead_paragraph: A case of considerable interest is not in course of investigation at the Mayor's Court, before Judge OSBORNE. The following are the facts: On Sunday afternoon last a gentleman called at the Chief's Office, and had an interview with one of the Chief's officers, at the same time showing the officer an advertisement offering a harp and a choice lot of music for sale at No. 75 Nassau-street.

headline.main: AN M. C. IN TROUBLE.; Verdict of Guilty. Consequences of Kissing Other Men's Wives. Trial of Wim, Valk for Assault and Battery.

docs.lead_paragraph: From the Evening Post. QUEENS COUNTY SESSIONS-HEMPSTEAD, June 5. Before Morris Fordick, County Judge; Geo. H. Horsefield and J. R. Morris, Justices of Sessions. The trial of Dr. Valk, Know-Nothing Member of Congress from the 'First District, for assault and battery on the person of Mrs. Mary Penfold, was commenced at the Court-House this morning.

docs.lead_paragraph: The rain we had hoped would so dampen the spirits of the people that there would not be so terrible a crowd at BARNUM'S yesterday as on Wednesday, but the desires of the people to be present seem to have started up fresher under the influence of the shower, like young radishes in their beds.
